$ Python: sys.stdin / sys.stdout / sys.stderr

{ Writing to stdout or to a file #stdout-or-file

  The following example writes to a file if the script was started with an argument (→ development/languages/Python/standard-library/sys#py-sys-argv[`sys.argv[1]`]) or to → development/stdin-stdout-stderr[stdout] otherwise.

  gh|about-python|/standard-library/sys/stdout_or_file.py||

  The script should be called with either of the two variants:
code {
$ python stdout_or_file.py
$ python stdout_or_file.py out.txt
code }

}

sa:
  → development/stdin-stdout-stderr
